    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER SERIES - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302536">Figure 36</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302536" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302536" filename="../figg13/G1302536.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Gear Shift Lever Assembly Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove boot from gear shift lever and secure assembly in vise with bottom of housing up.
                    Use a large screwdriver to twist between spring and housing, forcing spring from under lugs in the
                    housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302537">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
                    <emph type="bold">Do one coil at a time.</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302537" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302537" filename="../figg13/G1302537.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Force Spring From Under Lugs in Housing</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tension spring, washer and gear shift lever from the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302538">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302538" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302538" filename="../figg13/G1302538.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Remove Tension Spring, Washer and Gear Shift Lever</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the spade pin from the bore in the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302539">Figure 39</hotlnk>). If necessary, remove the O-ring from the groove
                    inside the tower.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302539" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302539" filename="../figg13/G1302539.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Remove Spade Pin From Bore in Housing Tower</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
